  "observation": "Orchestrator THINK: 3 ideas generated.",
  "suggestion": "[neuroscience+information-theory+Bayesian-brain] Precision-Weighted Prediction Error Engine. Every human response is a function of how much reality violated the person's expectations, weighted by how much that violation matters. Implement three scalars: predictionError (gap between expected and actual state), precision (arousal × personalRelevance × needRelevance), and weightedError = predictionError × precision. High weighted error → System 1 automatic response (fear, conformity reflex, avoidance). Low weighted error → System 2 deliberate evaluation. Emotion valence = threat vs. opportunity framing of the error. Behavior = minimization strategy (approach/avoid/update-belief). This single mechanism covers all 18 benchmarks: confirmation bias (minimize error by ignoring disconfirming), fear (survival prediction error, max precision), learned helplessness (expected error = zero agency → no action), anxiety loop (recursive error amplification), loss aversion (losses = larger error signal than equivalent gains). — Math: F = -log P(o|model) ≈ predictionError / precision; behavior = argmin_a E[F | a]; [motivational-psychology+social-psychology+control-theory] Drive Machine + Expectancy History (refinement, ready to implement). The Drive Machine reached fitness 0.369 but lacks history integration and social routing. Extend it: (1) Each unmet need generates a drive signal (intensity = 1 - satisfaction). (2) Drive is multiplied by perceivedControl from history — learned helplessness dampens competence/autonomy drives toward zero regardless of opportunity. (3) Route high-arousal stimuli to coping-style selection (trait-based: neuroticism → freeze/avoid, agreeableness → fawn, extraversion → approach). (4) Add social multiplier: in group settings, belonging-drive amplifies conformity pressure by groupSize × agreeableness. (5) Pick dominant drive → map to rootCause + behavior + emotion. This directly addresses the 5 benchmarks the Drive Machine likely missed: learned-helplessness, conformity, anxiety-loop, attachment-anxious, addiction-relapse. — Math: drive_i = needWeight_i × (1 - satisfaction_i) × perceivedControl_i; dominantDrive = argmax(drive_i); behavior = copingStyle[traits][dominantDrive]; [dynamical-systems+topology+physics+affective-neuroscience] Attractor Landscape Dynamics. Model psychological state as a 3D position (valence, arousal, agency). Personality traits define the shape of a potential energy landscape V(x) — stable personality types are broad basins, psychopathology is a shallow parasitic attractor. A stimulus applies a force vector displacing state. The system then relaxes: dx/dt = -∇V(x) + stimulus_force. Grief follows a forced traversal through sequential attractors (denial → anger → ... → acceptance). Addiction relapse is an old attractor with deep basin that pulls state back under stress. Anxiety loop is a limit cycle around a 'threat' attractor. This represents each person as their landscape shape (derived from personality traits + history), making it coherent and compact: one differential equation, personality = landscape curvature, history = added attractor wells. — Math: dx/dt = -∇V(x) + f(stimulus); V(x) = Σ_i w_i·(x - μ_i)² / σ_i where μ_i are attractor centers shaped by trait vector",
